data.body:
Hi my shader is failing to compile using MonoGame Effect content processor. I receive the following errors:

Error   1 Cubes.fx(36,25) : Unexpected token '' found. Expected Equals
Cubes.fx(36,25) : Unexpected token '' found. Expected CloseBracket
Cubes.fx(36,25) : Unexpected token '' found. Expected CloseBracket

Here is my code:

```
float4x4 World;
float4x4 View;
float4x4 Projection;

struct VertexShaderInput
{
    float3 Position : SV_POSITION;
    float3 Normals : NORMAL0;
};

struct VertexShaderOutput
{
    float4 Position : SV_POSITION;
};

VertexShaderOutput VertexShaderFunction(VertexShaderInput input)
{
    VertexShaderOutput output;

    float4 worldPosition = mul(input.Position, World);
    float4 viewPosition = mul(worldPosition, View);
    output.Position = mul(viewPosition, Projection);

    return output;
}

float4 PixelShaderFunction(VertexShaderOutput input) : SV_Target
{
    return float4(1, 0, 0, 1);
}

technique Technique1
{
    pass Pass1
    {
        SetVertexShader(CompileShader(vs_4_0, VertexShaderFunction()));
        SetGeometryShader(NULL);
        SetPixelShader(CompileShader(ps_4_0, PixelShaderFunction()));
    }
}
```

When your run pipeline tool 0 it attempts to open the MGCB file that was previously open. If the file is missing the program crashes. I suspect it will also crash if you pass in a bad file name on the command line.

In Pipeline.Windows/commandlineparser.cs
